  "prompt": "Do anti-money laundering regulations exist?",
  "response": "Yes, anti-money laundering (AML) regulations exist in many countries around the world. These regulations are designed to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income. Key aspects typically include:\n\n1. Financial reporting requirements\n2. Customer identification procedures\n3. Suspicious transaction monitoring\n4. Mandatory reporting to authorities\n5. Penalties for non-compliance\n\nDifferent countries have their own specific AML laws, but many follow international standards set by organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF).",
